<b translate="no" class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> 490024: Too many failing nozzles during PAINT recalibration</b> </title><abstract class="- topic/abstract " id="GUID-F19FDAAB-4DB0-4414-AD5D-D37FFFB17A78"><p class="- topic/p ">Too many nozzles failed on the mentioned printhead to be able to calculate the correct paint characteristics during re-calibration. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">No actions are required unless the print quality is out of specification</b>. 
</p></abstract><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-BE36AE82-9DEA-4782-AD56-FE2EEE04C944" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "> 
<b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b "> Collect</b> </title><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Calibration step</u> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This warning is generated during the calibration step: "PrintheadPAINtReference" which is part of the printhead calibration sequence. 
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<u class="+ topic/ph hi-d/u ">Patterns in calibration print</u> 
